<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2080</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                        Rice</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-05">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January
                                    6</hi>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have not failed
                                to communicate to my Government by telegram the substance of your
                                unofficial letter of to-day’s date requesting me to enquire of my
                                Government when you may expect its formal answer to your note of
                                October 21 on the subject of trade restrictions.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>